hese terms today? This essay questions whether this term used in diverse sources actually referred to any real entity or, if instead, it already served during the Middle Ages as an instrument for political and ideological agendas.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCivilization, Slavic. 0aMiddle Ages. 0aSlavsxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aSlavic peoples / medieval history. 4aSlawenbild. 4aSlawische Völker / Mittelalterliche Geschichte. 4aconception of slavic peoples. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2016z9783110485189oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831104882890 cprintz978311048814240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311049015240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110490152423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110490152.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEGb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016